com.eclipsesource.v8

Class V8Value

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.v8.V8Value
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Releasable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    V8Object

    public abstract class V8Value
extends Object
implements Releasable
    A base class for all V8 resources. V8 resources must be released. The rules for releasing resources is as follows: 1. If you created it, you must release it, with one exception; if the object is being passed pack via a return statement, the system will release it for you. 2. If the system created it, you donâ€™t need to worry about it, with one caveat; if the object was returned to you as a result of a method call, you must release it.

      • twin

        public V8Value twin()
        Creates a new Java object pointing at the same V8 Value as this. If the value is mutated (by adding new members or changing existing ones) then both the original and twin will be updated. Twins are .equal and .strict equals, but not == in Java. Twins must be released separately since they have their own native resources.
        Returns:
        A new Java object pointing at the same V8 Value as this.
